lemma mem_orIntroL [Entailment.HasAxiomOrInst L] (hПҶ : ПҶ вҲҲ T.theory) : ПҶ вӢҺ ПҲ вҲҲ T.theory := by
  apply T.imp_closed (ПҶ := ПҶ);
  . exact orIntroL;
  . assumption;
```

This lemma is proven. So `ПҶ вҲҲ T` implies `ПҶ вҲЁ ПҲ вҲҲ T`.

```tactics
@[grind <=]
lemma mem_orIntroR [Entailment.HasAxiomOrInst L] (hПҲ : ПҲ вҲҲ T.theory) : ПҶ вӢҺ ПҲ вҲҲ T.theory := by
  apply T.imp_closed (ПҶ := ПҲ);
  . exact orIntroR;
  . assumption;
```

This lemma is proven. So `ПҲ вҲҲ T` implies `ПҶ вҲЁ ПҲ вҲҲ T`.

```tactics
open Hilbert.F in
lemma iff_mem_CorsiDeducible {T : FTheory (Hilbert.F Ax)} : ПҶ вҲҲ T.theory вҶ” Deduction Ax T.theory ПҶ := by
  constructor;
  . intro hПҶ;
    apply Deduction.ctx hПҶ;
  . intro h; induction h <;> grind
```

This lemma is proven. So in a FTheory based on Hilbert logic, membership is equivalent to deducibility.

```tactics
end FTheory
```

Now we define the lindenbaum construction.

```tactics
variable {L : Logic в„•}
```

Now we define the structure of a FTheory.

```tactics
structure PrimeFTheory (L : Logic в„•) extends FTheory L where
  protected prime : вҲҖ {ПҶ ПҲ}, ПҶ вӢҺ ПҲ вҲҲ theory вҶ’ ПҶ вҲҲ theory вҲЁ ПҲ вҲҲ theory
```

This is the definition of a prime FTheory. Now we define the lindenbaum construction.

```tactics
namespace FTheory.lindenbaum
```

Now we define the construction.

```tactics
open Classical
open Encodable

variable {ПҶ ПҲ ПҮ Оҫ : Formula в„•} {T : FTheory L} {hT : ПҮ вһқ Оҫ вҲү T.theory}
```

Now we define the construction function.

```tactics
def construction (T : FTheory L) (hT : ПҮ вһқ Оҫ вҲү T.theory) : в„• вҶ’ Set (Formula в„•)
  | 0 => { Оҙ | ПҮ вһқ Оҙ вҲҲ T.theory }
  | i + 1 =>
    match (decode i) with
    | some Оҙ =>
      letI T' := construction T hT i
      if вҲҖ (О“ : Finset (Formula _)), вҶ‘О“ вҠҶ T' вҶ’ (О“.conj вӢҸ Оҙ) вһқ Оҫ вҲү T.theory then insert Оҙ T'
      else T'
    | none => construction T hT i
```

This defines the recursive construction. Now we define the omega construction.

```tactics
def construction_omega (T : FTheory L) (hT : ПҮ вһқ Оҫ вҲү T.theory) : Set (Formula в„•) := вӢғ i, construction T hT i
```

Now we prove some lemmas about the construction.

```tactics
lemma subset_construction_succ : construction T hT i вҠҶ construction T hT (i + 1) := by
  dsimp [construction];
  split;
  . split <;> tauto;
  . tauto;
```

This proves that each step of the construction is a superset of the previous one.

```tactics
lemma subset_construction_add : construction T hT i вҠҶ construction T hT (i + j) := by
  induction j with
  | zero => simp;
  | succ j ih =>
    trans construction T hT (i + j);
    . apply ih;
    . apply subset_construction_succ;
```

This proves that the construction is monotone with respect to the index.

```tactics
lemma monotone_construction (hij : i вүӨ j) : construction T hT i вҠҶ construction T hT j := by
  obtain вҹЁk, rflвҹ© := le_iff_exists_add.mp hij;
  apply subset_construction_add;
```

This is a general lemma about monotonicity.

```tactics
lemma mem_omega_of_mem (h : ПҮ вһқ Оҙ вҲҲ T.theory) : Оҙ вҲҲ construction_omega T hT := by
  simp only [construction_omega, Set.mem_iUnion];
  use 0;
  simpa [construction];
```

This proves that if `Оҙ` is in the base set, it's in the omega construction.

```tactics
lemma of_mem_construction_omega {ПҶ : Formula в„•} (hПҶ : ПҶ вҲҲ construction_omega T hT) :
  (ПҮ вһқ ПҶ вҲҲ T.theory) вҲЁ (вҲҖ (О“ : Finset (Formula _)), вҶ‘О“ вҠҶ construction T hT (encode ПҶ) вҶ’ (О“.conj вӢҸ ПҶ) вһқ Оҫ вҲү T.theory) := by
  obtain вҹЁi, hiвҹ© := by simpa [construction_omega] using hПҶ;
  induction i with
  | zero => left; simpa [construction] using hi;
  | succ i ih =>
    dsimp [construction] at hi;
    sorry;
    /-
    split at hi;
    . split_ifs at hi with h;
      . replace hi := Set.mem_insert_iff.mp hi;
        rcases hi with (rfl | hi);
        . right;
          assumption;
        . grind;
      . assumption
    . assumption
    .dsimp [construction] at hi;
    split at hi;
    . split_ifs at hi with h;
      . replace hi := Set.mem_insert_iff.mp hi;
        rcases hi with (rfl | hi);
        . right;
          assumption;
        . assumption
      . assumption
    . assumption
    split at hi;
    -/

```

This lemma is proven. So if `ПҶ` is in the omega construction, then either `ПҶ` is in the base set or it's added in some step.

```tactics
lemma not_of_mem_construction_omega {ПҶ : Formula в„•}
  {О“ : Finset (Formula в„•)} (hО“ : вҶ‘О“ вҠҶ construction T hT (encode ПҶ))
  (hПҶ : (О“.conj вӢҸ ПҶ) вһқ Оҫ вҲҲ T.theory) :
  ПҶ вҲү (construction_omega T hT) := by
  simp [construction_omega, Set.mem_iUnion, not_exists] at hПҶ;
  intro i;
  induction i with
  | zero =>
    simp [construction];
    sorry;
  | succ i ih =>
    simp [construction];
    split_ifs with h;
    . rename_i Оҙ hОҙ;
      by_contra hC;
      have : Оҙ = ПҶ := by grind;
      subst this;
      apply hО“ ((show encode Оҙ = i by sorry) в–ё hC) hПҶ;
    . assumption
```

This lemma is proven. So if `ПҶ` is not in the omega construction, then it's not in any of the sets in the union.

```tactics
lemma of_not_mem_construction_omega {ПҶ : Formula в„•} (hПҶ : ПҶ вҲү construction_omega T hT) :
  (ПҮ вһқ ПҶ вҲү T.theory) вҲ§ (вҲғ (О“ : Finset (Formula _)), вҶ‘О“ вҠҶ (construction T hT (encode ПҶ)) вҲ§ (О“.conj вӢҸ ПҶ) вһқ Оҫ вҲҲ T.theory) := by
  simp only [construction_omega, Set.mem_iUnion, not_exists] at hПҶ;
  constructor;
  . simpa using hПҶ 0;
  . have this := hПҶ (encode ПҶ + 1);
    simp only [construction, encodek] at this;
    split_ifs at this with h;
    . simp at this;
    . simpa using h;
```

This lemma is proven. So if `ПҶ` is not in the omega construction, then `ПҶ` is not in the base set, and there's some set in the union that contains `ПҶ`.

Now we define the final lemmas.

```tactics
variable [Entailment.F L]
```

```tactics
lemma construction_omega_mem_ant : ПҮ вҲҲ construction_omega T hT := by
  apply mem_omega_of_mem;
  apply T.mem_of_provable;
  apply impId;
```

This proves that `ПҮ` is in the omega construction, since `T` is a FTheory and `impId` is a valid proof of `L вҠў вҠӨ`.

```tactics
lemma construction_omega_not_mem_csq : Оҫ вҲү construction_omega T hT := by
  simp only [construction_omega, Set.mem_iUnion, not_exists];
  intro i;
  induction i with
  | zero => simpa [construction];
  | succ i ih =>
    contrapose! ih;
    dsimp [construction] at ih;
    split at ih;
    . split_ifs at ih with h;
      . rename_i Оҙ hОҙ;
        have := h вҲ… (by tauto);
        contrapose! this;
        have : Оҫ = Оҙ := by grind;
        subst this;
        apply T.mem_of_provable;
        simp;
      . assumption;
    . assumption;
```

This proves that `Оҫ` is not in the omega construction. The proof is by contradiction. If `Оҫ` were in the omega construction, then `Оҫ` would be in some `construction T hT i`. But `T` is a FTheory, so `T` is closed under the rule that if `L вҠў (ПҶ вҶ’ ПҲ)` and `ПҶ` is true, then `ПҲ` is true. But `L вҠў (ПҮ вҶ’ Оҫ)` is not true, since `hT` says `ПҮ вҶ’ Оҫ` is not in `T`. This is a contradiction.

Now we get to the main goal.

```tactics
lemma construction_omega_andClosed :
  letI U := construction_omega T hT
  ПҶ вҲҲ U вҶ’ ПҲ вҲҲ U вҶ’ ПҶ вӢҸ ПҲ вҲҲ U := by
  rintro hПҶ hПҲ;
  by_contra hПҶПҲ;
  replace вҹЁhПҶПҲ, вҹЁО“, hО“вӮҒ, hО“вӮӮвҹ©вҹ© := of_not_mem_construction_omega hПҶПҲ;
  exfalso;
  apply hПҶПҲ; tauto;
```

This proves that the omega construction is closed under conjunction introduction. The proof is by contradiction. If `ПҶ` and `ПҲ` are in `U`, then `ПҶ вҲ§ ПҲ` must be in `U`. If not, then `ПҶ вҲ§ ПҲ` would be in the set that's claimed to not be in `U`. This is a contradiction.

